# Experience

Our experience with this series of assignments was quite rocky -
there were a lot of moments where we struggled, but then there were some that were rather productive.

One thing that we wish we did differently is how we approached our implementations.
We often had to go back and edit things because we didn’t account for something.
This is especially clear if our submissions across assignment 5, 6, and 7 are compared.

The one thing we realised after getting the code from our providers is that having an interface
for the controller might have been more helpful, simply because when we had to use their
listeners and views, we felt the need to add another controller.

The one thing that made us feel good about our code was the fact that we did not have to make
any updates for our customers. Our entire experience with them was simply answering
questions regarding our code.

Our experience with our providers was good. They were very willing to answer questions and
explain their design choices. I would say that our main problem was the fact that their
ReadMe wasn’t helpful - it simply listed what the EditorView supported.
We had to spend quite a bit of time going through all the code given to us to understand their
arrangement of classes and determine what needs to be adapted.
